President Joe Biden delivered a speech on the South Lawn of the White House, addressing the importance of the trucking industry and its role in the country's economy. He thanked truck drivers for their hard work and acknowledged the challenges they face, such as long wait times and declining wages. Biden highlighted the efforts his administration has made to support the industry, including increasing the issuance of commercial driver's licenses and expanding apprenticeship programs. He also emphasized the need to recruit more women and people of color into the trucking workforce. The President discussed the importance of investing in American manufacturing and supply chains, and he referenced the recent passage of the Infrastructure Law, which will make significant investments in roads and bridges. Biden concluded by expressing his commitment to supporting truck drivers and their families and thanked them for their contributions to the nation.